mibatmpProfileTable.name: mibatmpProfileTable
mibatmpProfileTable.description: A list of mibatmpProfile profile entries.

mibatmpProfileEntry.name: mibatmpProfileEntry
mibatmpProfileEntry.description: A mibatmpProfile entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibatmpProfile profile.

atmpProfile_AgentMode.name: atmpProfile_AgentMode
atmpProfile_AgentMode.description: The valid modes for this ATMP agent.

atmpProfile_UdpPort.name: atmpProfile_UdpPort
atmpProfile_UdpPort.description: UDP port number to use locally.

atmpProfile_HomeAgentPassword.name: atmpProfile_HomeAgentPassword
atmpProfile_HomeAgentPassword.description: The password required to access this home agent.

atmpProfile_AtmpSapReply.name: atmpProfile_AtmpSapReply
atmpProfile_AtmpSapReply.description: Whether an ATMP Home Agent should reply to IPX SAP Nearest Server queries from the Mobile Client.

atmpProfile_RetryTimeout.name: atmpProfile_RetryTimeout
atmpProfile_RetryTimeout.description: The number of seconds between retries to establish a tunnel.

atmpProfile_RetryLimit.name: atmpProfile_RetryLimit
atmpProfile_RetryLimit.description: The maximum number of failed attempts to establish a tunnel before switching to the alternate home agent.

atmpProfile_IdleTimer.name: atmpProfile_IdleTimer
atmpProfile_IdleTimer.description: The number of minutes of no activity before an ATMP Home Agent will drop a tunnel. The value 0 disables the idle timer.

atmpProfile_MtuLimit.name: atmpProfile_MtuLimit
atmpProfile_MtuLimit.description: The maximum IP packet size that can be transmitted to a remote agent without performing pre-fragmentation. The value 0 disables this feature. If enabled, the smallest size the system will use is 68, even if a smaller size is specified. This is to comply with the minimum IP packet size requirement per RFC 791.

atmpProfile_ForceFragmentation.name: atmpProfile_ForceFragmentation
atmpProfile_ForceFragmentation.description: When set to NO, an ICMP message will be sent if a frame needs fragmentation and the DF bit is set. This is the standard behavior. When set to YES, it forces pre-fragmentation of large IP frames before they are sent to the remote agent, even if the frame has the DF bit set. This behavior is not standard and prevents MTU discovery mechanisms.

atmpProfile_AtmpSnmpTrap.name: atmpProfile_AtmpSnmpTrap
atmpProfile_AtmpSnmpTrap.description: When set to No, do not send ATMP SNMP traps. If Yes, send traps. The default is No.
